HomeDrew and Jonathan Scott Aren't the Stars of Their Latest Show, But You'll Still Want to Watch — Here's Why
By Megan SteinPosted on June 16, 2017 at 10:12am EDT 
ShareTweetEmail 





 




Drew and Jonathan Scott are coming to you in a new show — this time from behind the lens.
The 39-year-old twins and their production company, Scott Brothers Entertainment, are releasing the first series they’ve created that doesn’t star the massively popular siblings. Set to premiere June 19th on Discovery Family, Reno, Set Go! follows hosts Cheryl Torrenueva and Roger Morin as they secretly renovate homes for people in need.
“Reno, Set, Go! is a terrific show with a ton of heart and something the family can enjoy together,” Jonathan tells PEOPLE.
RELATED: Drew Scott and Fiancee Linda Phan Reveal Their New L.A. House: You Won’t Believe Its Bizarre Birthing Backstory





 Get to know contractor Roger Morin and designer Cheryl Torrenueva from our new original series RENO, SET, GO!  Don’t miss the series premiere of RENO, SET, GO! Monday, June 19th at 10PM ET only on Discovery Family. @cheryltorrenueva #DFCRenoSetGo
A post shared by Discovery Family (@discfamily) on May 30, 2017 at 6:23am PDT


“Cheryl and Roger were wonderful to work with and are a blast to watch,” Drew adds.
FROM PEN: How the Property Brothers Shocked Their Dad with Their Entrepreneurial Skills

Designer Torrenueva and contractor Morin, who Drew promises are “a blast to watch,” team up in each episode to give an unsuspecting homeowner, who’s been nominated by a spouse or family member, a room refresh in under 36 hours.
RELATED: The Men of MDLNY Face Off! Find Out Who’s Most Likely to Marry a Celeb, Cause a Public Scene and More
From a couple that’s struggling financially as they save for costly fertility treatments to a single dad who needs a man cave, each story will inevitably leave viewers teary eyed. Don’t believe us? Try to get through the exclusive preview above without scrambling for a tissue.
Reno, Set, Go! premieres with two back-to-back episodes on June 19th at 10:00 p.m. ET on Discovery Family.


